WEBVTT

00:00:01.490 --> 00:00:07.490
Do you own a car, or a motorbike, or some other type of vehicle?

00:00:07.490 --> 00:00:13.490
If you do, you realize that it brings with it a serious responsibility.

00:00:13.490 --> 00:00:21.489
Initially, it costs quite a bit of money to buy a vehicle, but also you need to keep on spending money to keep it running.

00:00:21.489 --> 00:00:28.489
In addition to that, there is another serious responsibility that comes with owning a vehicle.

00:00:28.489 --> 00:00:41.490
And that is the responsibility to maintain it safely, so that it doesn't break down, doesn't cause accidents, and most importantly doesn't cause loss of life.

00:00:41.490 --> 00:00:51.490
Of course, if you have a maintenance program, you're not just going to wait for something to fall off the vehicle, or perhaps for it just to stop.

00:00:51.490 --> 00:00:59.490
But rather ahead of time, you have to have a checklist to see that everything is working properly.

00:00:59.490 --> 00:01:09.489
Well, in a similar way, spiritually speaking, each one of us needs a maintenance program with regard to our spirituality.

00:01:09.489 --> 00:01:13.489
What sort of maintenance program are we talking about?

00:01:13.489 --> 00:01:22.489
Well, let's take our Bibles, please, and turn to the second book of Corinthians chapter 13 and verse 5.

00:01:22.489 --> 00:01:28.489
Second Corinthians chapter 13 and verse 5.

00:01:28.489 --> 00:01:34.489
There it says, keep testing whether you are in the faith.

00:01:34.489 --> 00:01:38.489
Keep proving what you yourselves are.

00:01:38.489 --> 00:01:46.489
Or do you not recognize that Jesus Christ is in union with you unless you are disapproved?

00:01:46.489 --> 00:01:53.489
So notice right in the beginning of that verse it says, keep testing, keep proving.

00:01:53.489 --> 00:01:55.489
What does that really mean?

00:01:55.489 --> 00:02:02.489
Well, if you look at this study note associated with verse 5, it tells us this.

00:02:02.489 --> 00:02:13.490
One lexicon states that the word Paul here uses for testing means to endeavour to discover the nature or character of something.

00:02:13.490 --> 00:02:25.490
They could discover the nature of their own spiritual standing by comparing their daily conduct, attitudes and decisions with the sacred truths they were taught.

00:02:25.490 --> 00:02:31.490
Doing such testing would help them to keep proving that they were true Christians.

00:02:31.490 --> 00:02:41.490
For proving, Paul uses a word that could refer to testing whether something is genuine as one might test metals.

00:02:41.490 --> 00:02:45.490
Do we see the point of what this verse tells us?

00:02:45.490 --> 00:02:52.490
As Christians, we need to keep testing continually that we are in the faith.

00:02:52.490 --> 00:02:56.490
But now, what does this word faith mean in this context?

00:02:56.490 --> 00:03:08.490
It's not just referring to the quality of faith, but rather it involves all the Christian teachings that we find in God's Word of the Bible.

00:03:08.490 --> 00:03:21.490
So having that in mind, keep testing, keep proving, really means that we need to look at ourselves and see if we're really living up to what the Bible tells us to do.

00:03:21.490 --> 00:03:25.490
Now that's a very serious maintenance program.

00:03:25.490 --> 00:03:38.490
But just as we do a maintenance program for a vehicle and we might have a checklist, is there a checklist that we can use when we're testing and proving that we're in the faith?

00:03:38.490 --> 00:03:42.490
Yes, there is. We can say there are three things.

00:03:42.490 --> 00:03:50.490
First of all, we need to ask heart-searching questions about our relationship with Jehovah.

00:03:50.490 --> 00:03:56.490
That's the first point. Ask the questions that will search through our heart.

00:03:56.490 --> 00:04:01.490
Secondly, we have to answer honestly.

00:04:01.490 --> 00:04:08.490
Yes, whatever we see is an answer to those questions, then we need to have a correct answer.

00:04:08.490 --> 00:04:26.490
And then finally, we need to seek Jehovah's help in making whatever adjustments we need to make so that we can maintain a spirituality strong and in good standing so that our relationship with Jehovah is good.

00:04:26.490 --> 00:04:35.490
So with that in mind, let's go back to the illustration we started with, a vehicle, a car or a motorbike.

00:04:35.490 --> 00:04:49.490
If you were to compare our Christian faith or our belief, our conduct to a vehicle and the need to maintain it, what sort of things would you make as a comparison?

00:04:49.490 --> 00:04:53.490
Well, perhaps the first thing we might think about is the engine.

00:04:53.490 --> 00:05:01.490
You certainly need to make sure the engine works correctly because that's what gives the vehicle the power to keep moving.

00:05:01.490 --> 00:05:12.490
So it's good for us to ask the question, what is it that moves us or motivates us so that we serve Jehovah acceptably?

00:05:12.490 --> 00:05:22.490
Well, the answer is found in the scriptures, and if we turn together to the first book of Timothy, chapter four and verse eight.

00:05:22.490 --> 00:05:28.490
That's first Timothy, chapter four and verse eight.

00:05:28.490 --> 00:05:35.490
See if you can discern what it is that we could liken to the engine in a car.

00:05:35.490 --> 00:05:53.490
It tells us, for physical training is beneficial for a little, but godly devotion is beneficial for all things as it holds promise of the life now and the life that is to come.

00:05:53.490 --> 00:06:00.490
Did you see what the scripture tells us is so important, godly devotion.

00:06:00.490 --> 00:06:04.490
But we need to understand what godly devotion is.

00:06:04.490 --> 00:06:11.490
In fact, we also need to appreciate this beautiful expression in the New World translation.

00:06:11.490 --> 00:06:17.490
Many other Bibles just simply translate this as godliness.

00:06:17.490 --> 00:06:30.490
Godliness is beneficial or perhaps they say godly training or being religious or even one version says mental training.

00:06:30.490 --> 00:06:42.490
But the New World translation captures the meaning of the original word here because you can train or program a robot to do a certain job.

00:06:42.490 --> 00:06:47.490
But you can't program it to have godly devotion. Why not?

00:06:47.490 --> 00:06:52.490
Because godly devotion involves how we feel about your hover.

00:06:52.490 --> 00:06:59.490
It means our loyalty to him based on a heart full of love and appreciation.

00:06:59.490 --> 00:07:10.490
So when it says godly devotion is important, it really involves why we do things, not just what we do.

00:07:10.490 --> 00:07:18.490
Well, let's think back to our illustration of the vehicle and you want to test the engine.

00:07:18.490 --> 00:07:23.490
What would you do to check the engine to see if it's okay?

00:07:23.490 --> 00:07:31.490
Well, one thing you might do is keep an eye on the temperature gauge because if the engine is overheating, you know there's a problem.

00:07:31.490 --> 00:07:36.490
Or perhaps you might check the oil to see if there's enough oil.

00:07:36.490 --> 00:07:41.490
Or you may check to see if you've changed the oil regularly enough.

00:07:41.490 --> 00:07:50.490
Or when the engine is idling, you might listen carefully to it to see if it's running smoothly or roughly.

00:07:50.490 --> 00:07:55.490
And of course you'd be interested if there's any strange sounds or noises.

00:07:55.490 --> 00:08:04.490
So that's the type of thing you would have on a checklist when you're trying to see if an engine is working properly.

00:08:04.490 --> 00:08:07.490
Now, none of that applies to godly devotion, does it?

00:08:07.490 --> 00:08:17.490
But what could be on our checklist for us to test godly devotion to see if it's healthy and strong or not?

00:08:17.490 --> 00:08:19.490
Well, again, the Bible helps us.

00:08:19.490 --> 00:08:28.490
If you turn with me this time to the book of Psalms, let's look at Psalm 40 and verse 8.

00:08:28.490 --> 00:08:33.490
That's Psalm 40 and verse 8.

00:08:33.490 --> 00:08:40.490
Here it tells us, to do your will, oh my God, is my delight.

00:08:40.490 --> 00:08:44.490
And your law is deep within me.

00:08:44.490 --> 00:08:50.490
Now, this is a test of our godly devotion. How so?

00:08:50.490 --> 00:09:01.490
Well, we need to ask ourselves, is my service to God something that I really delight in or is it simply a chore?

00:09:01.490 --> 00:09:08.490
Is it something that I do as a mere routine, something that I just keep on doing regularly,

00:09:08.490 --> 00:09:14.490
but don't really have a strong desire to accomplish it?

00:09:14.490 --> 00:09:21.490
Well, if we were thinking that our godly devotion was not so good, not so strong,

00:09:21.490 --> 00:09:29.490
perhaps we were just doing things out of routine rather than for our love for Jehovah, we need to take action.

00:09:29.490 --> 00:09:37.490
Just the same as if we heard that the engine had a knocking sound or if we saw that it was overheating.

00:09:37.490 --> 00:09:45.490
And that's exactly what Jesus told the brothers back in the first century in the congregation in Ephesus.

